The economic climate has continued to deteriorate to its previous low - never before has it been so high, with 41 percent of those who specifically judged the country’s economic situation to be very bad, while another 46 percent said it was rather bad.
Families are now again more pessimistic about the changes in their financial situation after the more hopeful prospects of spring and summer.
For the next year, the larger half of the population expects further deterioration and only a tenth improvement.
In December, more than all previous Gallup surveys, 71% of those surveyed felt that the Prime Minister was doing his job more badly than well.
In Ferenc Gyurcsány, 13 per cent of the respondents trust or have high confidence, while in Viktor Orbán, 38 per cent are supporters.
