The average increase in HUF was 1480.
Last year, the average price increase was 1206 forints, so that the rise in VAT in prices felt its effect last Christmas.
It was precisely this process that disrupted trade, apparently the stores were unable to decide how much margin they would apply to a product, as they were unable to calculate the impact of price changes on consumption.
(If a trader designs the rotational speed of a product incorrectly, he may lose a significant profit on the margin adjusted to the traffic intensity.)
Due to VAT, the price increase of the Daily Basket was so extreme last year that the most expensive one was 1720 forints more than in 2006, while the cheapest one was only 844 forints.
This year this extreme did not show itself, as the most expensive one was 1630 forints more than last year, and the cheapest one was 1284 forints more expensive.
