NHS committees must verify the qualifications and work experience of their overseas employees before starting employment, as well as their availability of the necessary permits to work in the United Kingdom.
Although the Scottish health committees use Disclosure Scotland to verify criminal records, the agency is not authorized to obtain such information from outside the UK.
The report of the Chief Auditor suggested, inter alia, that the committees should introduce a guide to the Criminal Records Office, which would facilitate the employer’s verification processes with the various overseas countries.
"Although we found evidence of such checks in staff records, they are not regularly carried out," the report said.
